    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm looking at some new senior food for my lab (he's 9 now) and it's got a pretty high protein count. i was wondering what a good protein to fat ratio would be for an older lab to keep his weight down but keep his muscle up? thanks",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For a senior Labrador, a balanced protein to fat ratio is key to maintaining lean muscle while managing weight. Aiming for a food that is high in quality protein—around 25-30% if you're looking at the protein percentage—while keeping fat relatively controlled is often a good strategy. This helps support muscle mass without adding excessive calories that could lead to weight gain. Always consult with your veterinarian before making significant changes to your dog's diet.",
      "source": "target",
