    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. does the type of protein matter though? like is there a big difference between using chicken or beef for an older dog, or does it just come down to the actual percentage in the bag?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The type of protein definitely matters, as different sources offer varying nutrient profiles. While the percentage is important for overall calorie control, quality matters because it dictates the amino acid profile available for your dog. Chicken and beef both provide excellent proteins, but beef might offer more iron and B vitamins, whereas chicken can sometimes be easier for sensitive stomachs. Look for high-quality, recognizable sources listed first in the ingredients list.",
      "source": "target",
