    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "makes sense. i'll check the labels for that. what about fats? i see some things mentioning fish oil or omega fatty acids. is that actually necessary for an older dog or is it just marketing hype?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Omega fatty acids, especially from fish oil, are not just marketing hype; they offer significant benefits for older dogs. These essential fatty acids are crucial for maintaining healthy skin, a shiny coat, and, most importantly, supporting joint health by reducing inflammation. For senior dogs, which are prone to aches and arthritis, this anti-inflammatory benefit can be quite valuable. It's a nutrient that your dog's body cannot produce on its own, making it genuinely necessary.",
      "source": "target",
